              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE:HIGH",
              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:User-controlled query parameter keys from `Request.Query.Keys` are assigned to `param` if a specific query value is found. This tainted `param` then flows into `DoSomething` (which is assumed to be a passthrough) and is subsequently used unencoded as the format string in `string.Format(bar, obj)`. The result is rendered directly into the HTML response via `Content()`, allowing Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). The `X-XSS-Protection` header is explicitly disabled, further exposing the vulnerability."
            ]
          },
