              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE:HIGH",
              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:User-controlled input from `request.args.get('BenchmarkTest01306')` or `request.form.get('BenchmarkTest01306')` flows into the `param` variable. This input then passes through `test_instance.do_something(param)` which is an identity transformation, making `bar` also user-controlled. The value of `bar` is directly interpolated into the SQL query string via an f-string at line 63 (`sql = f\"SELECT ... PASSWORD='{bar}'\"`). This creates a SQL Injection vulnerability because the `cursor.execute()` call at line 71 executes an already malformed query string. Although a placeholder `?` is used for the USERNAME part, the PASSWORD part remains vulnerable due to string concatenation before the query is executed."
            ]
